class Solution {
    public int subtractProductAndSum(int n) {
        int product = 1;
        int sum = 0;
        while (n > 0) {
            int digit = n % 10;
            product *= digit;
            sum += digit;
            n /= 10;
        }
        return product - sum;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates through each digit of the input number, calculating the product and sum of the digits. It uses a constant amount of space and has a time complexity proportional to the number of digits in the input number.
